testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The parents have decided to name firstborn BabyG Quinn 'Jenna Marie Quinn'. An update to the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate is submitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Birth Registration System.


Comments

None


Pre-condition

A prior message has been submitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Birth Registration System with preliminary information from the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate without a chosen name for the baby.


Post-Condition

The parents have updated the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate, and the updated information has been transmitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Electronic Birth Registration System. 


Test Objectives

This test step verifies the conformance of a fully populated  electronic HL7 message (HL7 Version 2.6 Implementation Guide: Vital Records Birth and Fetal Death Reporting, Release 1 STU Release 2: Revise Provider Supplied Mother's Live Birth Information (PSMLBIA08)) update using the updated information provided in the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate.


Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the updated Provider Supplied Mother's Live Birth Information (PSMLBIA08) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.

testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The facilities worksheet is updated with additional clinical issues documented for the mother prior to hospital discharge indicating that the mother had returned to the Operating Room for an unplanned operation following the delivery. An update to the Facility's Worksheet for Live Birth Certificate is submitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Birth Registration System.


Comments

None.


Pre-condition

A prior message has been submitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Birth Registration System with preliminary information from the Facilities Worksheet for the Live Birth Certificate with preliminary clinical information for the baby. Additional relevant clinical information is available for the newborn which must be conveyed to the jurisdiction.

The birth clerk has updated the Facility's Worksheet for the Live Birth Certificate, and the updated information has been transmitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Electronic Birth Registration System.

Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the Provider Supplied Facility's Live Birth Information (PSFLBIA08) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.

testSteps.name: Transmit Revised Combined Report of Live Birth
testSteps.description: Update and validate the message that is transmitted to convey the combined Mother's Worksheet information and Facility's Worksheet information from the hospital of birth to the jurisdiction.

testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The parents have decided to name firstborn BabyG Quinn 'Jenna Marie Quinn', and The facilities worksheet is updated with additional clinical issues documented for the mother prior to hospital discharge indicating that the mother had returned to the Operating Room for an unplanned operation following the delivery. The BIS verifies that the updated record is complete and accurate before submitting an update to the Combined Report of Live Birth to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Birth Registration System. The EBRS record is saved, additional EBRS processing completed, and the record is filed electronically by the EBRS with the state vital statistics office.


Comments

Pre-condition

A prior message has been submitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Birth Registration System with preliminary combined information from the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate without a chosen name for the baby, and with preliminary clinical information for the baby in the Facilities Worksheet for the Live Birth Certificate. Additional relevant clinical information is available for the mother indicating that she had returned to the Operating Room for an unplanned operation following the delivery which must be conveyed to the jurisdiction.



Post-Condition

The parents have updated the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate, and the birth clerk has updated the Facility's Worksheet for the Live Birth Certificate. The updated combined information has been transmitted to the Jurisdiction Vital Records Electronic Birth Registration System. 


Test Objectives

This test step verifies the conformance of a fully populated  electronic HL7 message (HL7 Version 2.6 Implementation Guide: Vital Records Birth and Fetal Death Reporting, Release 1 STU Release 2: Revise Provider Supplied Live Birth Information (PSLBIA08)) update using the updated information provided in the Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate and the updated Facility Worksheet for the Live Birth Certificate.


Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the Provider Supplied Live Birth Information (PSLBIA08) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.

Description

The birth information specialist (BIS) logs into the EMR and accesses the record for the firstborn of Jada’s newborn baby girls. The EMR presents the Facility’s Worksheet (FWS) form to the BIS which contains some data that has been pre-populated such as mother’s height and pre-pregnancy weight and mother and father’s age. The BIS reviews the form, and completes the remaining items, which include all of the data items that pertain to Jada’s prenatal care and pregnancy history such as the date of her first prenatal visit, which was July 20, 2018 and the date that her last normal menses began, which was June 5, 2018. Jada’s gestational hypertension was also noted as a risk factor in the pregnancy.

Jada already has one child so the “number of previous live births now living” item on the worksheet is noted as “1” and the “number of previous live births now dead” is set recorded as “0”. The date of Jada’s last live birth is recorded as November 2014. Jada and James had difficulty conceiving this time around and tried IVF to initiate the pregnancy. This pregnancy resulted from that treatment and this was noted on the Facility’s Worksheet. The number of infants in this deliver born alive is set to "2", the plurality value is also "2" and the birth order for this baby is set to "1". The BIS also noted that Jada had no infections present and/or treated during the pregnancy. It is also noted that Jada attempted to deliver vaginally, but after an unsuccessful external cephalic version, her physician ultimately decided that a Cesarean was necessary.

The Facility’s Worksheet also includes the data items collected during her labor and delivery. The birth hospital is recorded as “South Hospital” and the Facility id is recorded as “5555512”. The attending physician is noted to be an M.D, and his N.P.I. is 112237003. Jada’s pregnancy was induced due to indications of fetal distress and during the delivery, the birth attendant diagnosed the fetuses with neonatal sepsis due to chorioamnionitis and administered antibiotics to Jada during labor. As labor progressed, the physician decided that the babies weren't tolerating the labor well and spinal anesthesia was administered to Jada, to prepare for a Cesarean. The BIS noted all of these details in the FWS along with evidence of heavy meconium staining in the amniotic fluid. In spite of these difficulties during labor, both Jada and her two baby girls had a good outcome and both maternal morbidity and congenital anomalies of the newborn are noted as “none”.

The BIS captures data relating to the newborn, such as firstborn baby Quinn’s date of birth, time of birth (which was 1:00 PM) and the method of delivery. Jada’s weight at delivery is noted to be 175 lbs.  The obstetric gestation estimate is recorded as 36 weeks. This baby’s 5 minute Apgar score is recorded as “5” and her 10 minute Apgar score is “7”. After a short stay in the NICU where firstborn baby girl Quinn continued to receive antibiotics to treat her infection, she was cleared to go home with her parents and her twin sister. The BIS notes this in the Facility’s Worksheet along with all of the data items that need to be collected for the newborn, such as baby’s birthweight which is 8lbs 1oz.. The BIS notes that firstborn baby girl Quinn is happily alive and breastfeeding at the time of discharge. This completes the Facility’s Worksheet.

Description

On Feb 12th, 2019, Jada Ann Quinn has given birth to baby girl twins at a hospital in Salt Lake City, UT. The birth information specialist (BIS) asks Jada to complete the Mother’ Worksheet for Child’s Birth Certificate, but Jada isn’t feeling well so she has her husband James complete this form. James enters Jada’s full legal name and checks the box on the Mother’s Worksheet to indicate that the couple hasn’t chosen names for the two baby girls yet. He enters the address of the couple’s residence at 1848 South 1300 East in Salt Lake City, UT 84401. James checks the two boxes which indicate that this residence is inside the city limits and that it is the same as the mailing address. James enters Jada’s birthdate, which is 1/15/1985 and indicates that Jada was born in Utah.

James indicates that Jada has a professional degree in the checkbox under education and checks the box which indicates that Jada is not Spanish/Hispanic or Latina. He checks the boxes which indicate that Jada’s race is white and American Indian. She is 5’6’’ and her pre-pregnancy weight was 145 lbs. She didn’t receive assistance from WIC during this pregnancy.

Prior to becoming pregnant, Jada was a 1 pack per day smoker. At her physician’s urging she managed to cut down to 3 cigarettes per day during her first trimester and 1 per day during her second trimester. She had stopped altogether by her third trimester! Good job Jada!

James checks the box on the Mother’s Worksheet to indicate that Jada had been married and noted that her maiden name was King. He checks the box which indicated that the paternity acknowledgement had been completed. He enters his full name, James Brandon Quinn, as the legal name of the twins father and enters 1/4/1988 for his birthdate. He indicates that he was born in the UK and he has a professional degree as well.

James checks the box on the form to indicate that he is not Spanish/Hispanic or Latino and also checks the box which indicates that his race is white. James enters Jada’s SSN which is 132-22-5986 and his own which is 132-22-5421. He also checks the box indicating that the parents want an SSN issued for each of the babies. He signs and dates the form and lists his full name as the person who is providing the information for the form. Finally, James checks the box indicating that his relationship to the twins mother is that of the father and this completes the Mother’s Worksheet.

testSteps.name: Transmit Live Birth Report From Jurisdiction to NCHS
testSteps.description: This test step is used to create and validate the transaction sent from the Jurisdiction to NCHS for the Report of Live Birth

testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The jurisdictional vital records (JVR) office has received the report of live birth from the EHR for Jada's baby girl. The JVR office validates many of the date items that they receive from the EHR.

The mother's birth date and father's birth date are validated along with the mother's height, pre-pregnancy weight and delivery weight. The mother's and father's education level values are validated.

Some of the values associated with the mother's medical information such as the estimate of gestation, the number of prenatal care visits and the number of previous Cesareans are validated by the JVR office.

Data items recorded by the EHR during labor and delivery such as the plurality  and the baby's birth weight are validated as well.

Coded result values are sent to NCHS which indicate whether each of these validations were performed and if they passed or failed. These values, along with most of the data collected at the EHR are sent to 

NCHS along with the date that the birth registration occurred. This data is sent to NCHS in the form of an HL7 v2.6 birth reporting A04 message. Some data items  are collected by the EHR but do not get 

transferred to NCHS. These include the name of the birth facility and the infant's name, parent's names, addresses, social security numbers, telephone numbers and any other PII.


Comments

None


Pre-condition

The jurisdiction has received a report of the newborn, Baby Quinn. 



Post-Condition

The birth information has been transmitted from the Jurisdiction Vital Records Electronic Birth Registration System to NCHS.

Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the Jurisdiction Live Birth Information (JLBIA04) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.

testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The jurisdictional vital records (JVR) office has received an updated report of live birth from the EHR for Jada's baby girl indicating that the parents have decided to name firstborn 'BabyG Quinn' 'Jenna Marie Quinn'. The JVR office has also received an update to the facilities worksheet with additional clinical issues documented for the mother prior to hospital discharge indicating that the mother had returned to the Operating Room for an unplanned operation following the delivery. The JVR office re-validates many of the date items that they receive from the EHR before transmitting the revised live birth report from the JVR office to NCHS.

The mother's birth date and father's birth date are validated along with the mother's height, pre-pregnancy weight and delivery weight. The mother's and father's education level values are validated.

Some of the values associated with the mother's medical information such as the estimate of gestation, the number of prenatal care visits and the number of previous Cesareans are validated by the JVR office.

Data items recorded by the EHR during labor and delivery such as the plurality  and the baby's birth weight are validated as well.

Coded result values are sent to NCHS which indicate whether each of these validations were performed and if they passed or failed. These values, along with most of the data collected at the EHR are sent to 

NCHS along with the date that the birth registration occurred. This data is sent to NCHS in the form of an HL7 v2.6 birth reporting A04 message. Some data items  are collected by the EHR but do not get 

transferred to NCHS. These include the name of the birth facility and the infant's name, parent's names, addresses, social security numbers, telephone numbers and any other PII.


Comments

None


Pre-condition

The jurisdiction has received a revised report of the newborn, Baby Quinn indicating the chosen name and updating the maternal morbidity to indicate an unplanned visit to the operating room following delivery.



Post-Condition

The revised birth information has been transmitted from the Jurisdiction Vital Records Electronic Birth Registration System to NCHS.


Test Objectives

This test step verifies the conformance of a fully populated  electronic HL7 messages (HL7 Version 2.6 Implementation Guide: Vital Records Birth and Fetal Death Reporting, Release 1 STU Release 2: Revise Jurisdiction Live Birth Information (JLBIA08)) using the information submitted to the jurisdiction from the provider from the Revised Mother's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate and the information submitted from the Revised Facility Worksheet for the Live Birth Certificate.


Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the Revise Jurisdiction Live Birth Information (JLBIA08) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.

testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The EMR birth clerk, Jessica Leung, accesses the Facility’s Fetal Death Worksheet (FWS) form which contains some data that has been pre-populated such as mother’s height and pre-pregnancy weight and mother and father’s age. The clerk reviews the form, and completes the remaining items, which include all of the data items that pertain to Carmen’s prenatal care and pregnancy history such as the date of her first prenatal visit, which was May 18, 2018 and the date that her last normal menses began, which was April 18, 2018. Carmen had 8 prenatal visits for this pregnancy. She had not planned to deliver at home and Jessica Leung checked the appropiate box to indicate this on the FWS. Carmen’s gestational diabetes and hypertensive disorder were noted as a risk factors in the pregnancy. Also, the fact that Carmen had previously had one Cesarean was noted as a risk factor.

Carmen already has one child so the “number of previous live births now living” item on the worksheet is noted as “1” and the “number of previous live births now dead” is checked as "none".. The date of Carmen’s last live birth is recorded as January 28, 2016. Unfortunately, Carmen had one previous pregnancy in February 2014 which didn’t result in a live birth and the clerk noted this on the FWS. The clerk also noted that Carmen had a Chlamydia infection present and/or treated during the pregnancy. 

The Facility’s Worksheet also includes the data items collected during her labor and delivery. The birth hospital is recorded as “South Hospital” and the Facility id is recorded as “0290 CADOH FI”. It is noted that Carmen was transferred to South Hospital from Main Hospital due to fetal indications for delivery, The attending physician is noted to be Dr. Janet Seito, M.D, and her N.P.I. is 112247003. Carmen’s labor was spontaneous and she delivered a stillborn anencephalic female fetus weighing 1530 grams on 02/12/2019 at 02:29 AM . There was no attempt to deliver the fetus using forceps or vacuum extraction and this was noted on the form. The delivery presentation was breech and Carmen delivered vaginally. She required a blood transfusion during the delivery. The obstetric gestation estimate was 20 weeks. Carmen's weight at delivery is recorded as 210 lbs. The "Burial" checkbox is checked on the form, to indicate the method of disposition. The initiating cause of the fetal death is documented as "Spontaneous Abortion" and "Placental insufficiency" is noted as a maternal condition that contributed to the cause of death, The estimated time of fetal death is documented to indicate that the fetus died during labor, after the first assessment. Description

On January 09, 2019, Carmen Teresa Lee is transferred into a local hospital because she is experiencing symptoms of early labor in her 2nd trimester of pregnancy.  Sadly, Carmen’s unborn fetus does not survive. Her husband, Tom Lee accompanied her to the hospital and he fills out the following items on the Patient’s Worksheet (PWS). Tom enters Carmen’s full legal name He enters the address of the couple’s residence at 3670 Miller Road Ann Arbor, MI 48103 and checks the box which indicates that this residence is the same as the mailing address and also checks the box which indicates that the household is inside city limits. Tom enters Carmen’s birth date, which is 2/15/1986 and her age, which is 33. He indicates that Carmen’s maiden name was Santos and that she was born in Puerto Rico. He indicates that Carmen was married during this pregnancy. 

Tom indicates that Carmen’s highest level of education is High School Graduate and checks the box which indicates that Carmen is Spanish/Hispanic or Latina. He checks the boxes which indicate that Carmen’s race is African American and Asian. Tom notes that Carmen did not receive WIC during this pregnancy.

Carmen was not a smoker and Tom noted on the PWS that Carmen didn’t smoke prior to the pregnancy or any time during the pregnancy. testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

The jurisdictional vital records (JVR) office has received the report of fetal death from the EHR for Carmen's delivery. The JVR office validates many of the date items that they receive from the EHR.

Coded result values are sent to NCHS which indicate whether data edits from validations were performed and if they passed or failed. These values, along with most of the data collected at the EHR are sent to NCHS via an HL7 v2.6 A04 message for the jurisdiction fetal death information.


Comments

None


Pre-condition

The jurisdiction has received a report of the fetal death for Carmen's delivery. 


Post-Condition

The fetal death information has been transmitted from the Jurisdiction Vital Records Electronic Birth Registration System to NCHS.


Test Objectives

This test step verifies the conformance of a fully populated  electronic HL7 messages (HL7 Version 2.6 Implementation Guide: Vital Records Birth and Fetal Death Reporting, Release 1 STU Release 2: Jurisdiction Fetal Death Information (JFDIA04)) using the information submitted to the jurisdiction from the provider from the Patient's Worksheet for Child's Birth Certificate and the information submitted from the Facility Worksheet for the Report of Fetal Death.


Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the Jurisdiction Fetal Death Information (JFDIA04) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.


Notes

testSteps.name: Transmit Void Certificate Report From Jurisdiction to NCHS for Live Birth
testSteps.description: This test step is used to create and validate the transaction sent from the Jurisdiction to NCHS for a Live Birth void certificate report

testStory.name: TestStory
testStory.html:
Description

Due to a paper jam and unreadable printed copy of the birth certificate, a Void certificate report is sent from the Jurisdiction to NCHS.


Comments

None


Pre-condition

The a prior report of live birth was sent to NCHS. The certificate number submitted previously to NCHS is no longer valid.


Post-Condition

The Void Certificate request has been received by NCHS.


Test Objectives

This test step verifies the conformance of a fully populated  electronic HL7 messages (HL7 Version 2.6 Implementation Guide: Vital Records Birth and Fetal Death Reporting, Release 1 STU Release 2: Revise Jurisdiction Live Birth Information (JVLBIA04)) using the certificate number for the record to be voided.


Evaluation Criteria

The  content of the Void Live Birth Certificate Information (JVLBIA04) correctly reflects the test data (context-based) in accordance with the Test Data Specification and the Message Content.


Notes
